--- title: "Data Visualization" author: "Corinna Boenke" --- # Challenge 4 ##Load librarys ::: {.cell hash='04_data_visualization_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-1_73ce3fae7ac21afb19220c1cf48db650'} ```{.r .cell-code} library(conflicted) library(tidyverse) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> ── Attaching core tidyverse packages ──────────────────────── tidyverse 2.0.0 ── #> ✔ dplyr 1.1.2 ✔ readr 2.1.4 #> ✔ forcats 1.0.0 ✔ stringr 1.5.0 #> ✔ ggplot2 3.4.2 ✔ tibble 3.2.1 #> ✔ lubridate 1.9.2 ✔ tidyr 1.3.0 #> ✔ purrr 1.0.1 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} library(vroom) library(data.table) library(furrr) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> Lade nötiges Paket: future ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} library(tictoc) library(readxl) library(readr) library(ggplot2) library("ggthemes") library(dplyr) library(lubridate) library(plotly) library(maps) conflicts_prefer(dplyr::filter) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> [conflicted] Will prefer dplyr::filter over any other package. ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} conflicts_prefer(lubridate::month) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> [conflicted] Will prefer lubridate::month over any other package. ``` ::: ::: ## Get Data ::: {.cell hash='04_data_visualization_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-2_894adba93001af19d49e1c8a94a4ffd5'} ```{.r .cell-code} covid_data_tbl <- read_csv("https://covid.ourworldindata.org/data/owid-covid-data.csv") ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> Rows: 311568 Columns: 67 #> ── Column specification ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> Delimiter: "," #> chr (4): iso_code, continent, location, tests_units #> dbl (62): total_cases, new_cases, new_cases_smoothed, total_deaths, new_dea... #> date (1): date #> #> ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data. #> ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message. ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} cummulative_covid_data_tbl <- covid_data_tbl %>% mutate(month_name = lubridate::month(date, label = TRUE, abbr = FALSE)) %>% mutate(year = lubridate::year(date)) %>% select(year, month_name, total_cases, location) %>% filter(year %in% c("2022")) %>% filter(location == 'Germany' | location == 'United Kingdom' | location == 'Spain' | location == 'France' | location == 'United States') %>% group_by(location, month_name) %>% summarize(all_cases = sum(total_cases)) %>% mutate(cummulative_cases = cumsum(all_cases)) %>% ungroup() %>% rename(Countries = location) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> `summarise()` has grouped output by 'location'. You can override using the #> `.groups` argument. ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} cummulative_covid_data_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ## Plot data ::: {.cell hash='04_data_visualization_cache/html/plot_01d2638edcdb75cc664da5875b5f6bf6'} ```{.r .cell-code} cummulative_covid_data <- as.data.frame(cummulative_covid_data_tbl) cummulative_covid_data ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # Setup canvas ggplot(cummulative_covid_data, aes(month_name, cummulative_cases)) + # Geometries geom_line(aes(x = month_name, y = cummulative_cases, group = Countries, color = Countries ))+ # Formatting scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::unit_format(scale = 1e-6, accuracy = 0.1, prefix = "", suffix = "M")) + labs( title = paste("COVID-19 confirmed cases worldwide"), subtitle = paste("As of 19/04/2022"), x = "Year 2022", y = "Cummulative Cases" ) + geom_smooth() + theme_fivethirtyeight() + theme_minimal() + theme( legend.position = "bottom", plot.title = element_text(face="bold"), plot.caption = element_text(face = "bold.italic") ) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x' ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](04_data_visualization_files/figure-html/plot-1.png){width=960} ::: ::: # Challenge 5 ## Plot data ::: {.cell hash='04_data_visualization_cache/html/plot_2_8287e337d77c3c8888fe17a738f528d6'} ```{.r .cell-code} mortality_rate_tbl <- covid_data_tbl %>% select(location, total_deaths, population) %>% group_by(location, population) %>% summarize(all_deaths = sum(total_deaths)) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(mortality_rate = all_deaths/population) %>% mutate(across(location, str_replace_all, "_", " ")) %>% #Hint mutate(location = case_when( location == "United Kingdom" ~ "UK", location == "United States" ~ "USA", location == "Democratic Republic of Congo" ~ "Democratic Republic of the Congo", TRUE ~ location )) %>% #distinct() filter(!is.na(mortality_rate)) %>% rename(country = location) %>% select(country, mortality_rate) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> `summarise()` has grouped output by 'location'. You can override using the #> `.groups` argument. ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> Warning: There was 1 warning in `mutate()`. #> ℹ In argument: `across(location, str_replace_all, "_", " ")`. #> Caused by warning: #> ! The `...` argument of `across()` is deprecated as of dplyr 1.1.0. #> Supply arguments directly to `.fns` through an anonymous function instead. #> #> # Previously #> across(a:b, mean, na.rm = TRUE) #> #> # Now #> across(a:b, \(x) mean(x, na.rm = TRUE)) ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} #World Map world <- map_data("world") mortality_rate_tbl %>% ggplot() + geom_map(map = world, aes(map_id = country, fill = mortality_rate)) + expand_limits(x=world$long, y=world$lat) + labs( title = paste("Confirmed COVID-19 deaths relative to the size of the population"), subtitle = paste("Around 6.2 Million confirmed COVID-19 deaths worldwide"), fill = "Mortality Rate", x = "", y = "", caption = "Date: 04/16/2021" ) + scale_fill_gradient(low='#FF0000',high='#800000', name='Mortality Rate') + theme(legend.position = "right", axis.text=element_blank(), axis.text.x=element_blank(), axis.ticks.x=element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](04_data_visualization_files/figure-html/plot_2-1.png){width=960} ::: :::
